OL,4,Csentence
OL,6,FBut the judge added the financial and
OL,7,Freputational damage Edwards suffered
OL,8,Fwas "the natural consequence of your
OL,9,Fbehaviour which you brought upon
OL,10,Fyourself".
OL,12,FHe continued: "I am of the clear view
OL,13,Fthat you do not present a risk or
OL,14,Fdanger to the public at large,
OL,15,Fspecifically to children.
OL,17,F"There is a realistic prospect of
OL,18,Frehabilitation."
OL,20,FThe judge declined to make a sexual
OL,21,Fharm prevention order against Edwards.
