OL,4,Csentence
OL,6,FWhen asked about his opinion on
OL,7,Fsuspended sentences in such cases and
OL,8,Fwhether he would consider a review, he
OL,9,Freplied: "As far as the sentence is
OL,10,Fconcerned, I mean, that is for the
OL,11,Fcourt to decide, having looked at all
OL,12,Fthe available evidence.
OL,14,F"I have also been busy all day so I
OL,15,Fhaven't looked at it, and I'm not
OL,16,Fgoing to get into the business of
OL,17,Fcommenting on court sentences. That is
OL,18,Fa matter for the court.
OL,20,F"But was I shocked by what I have seen
OL,21,Fand heard? You bet I was."
